      "message": "@gary The queries are based on the scope of 89179 commit\n\nFor runtime-added devices, the expectation is that only the newly discovered device should be processed and attested. We do not intend to re-attest all previously discovered devices whenever a new endpoint is detected. \nTherefore, when a new responder is discovered at runtime, the discovery layer should notify the manager with the specific ResponderInfo for that device through a single-device entry point `notifyDeviceAdded`. This allows the manager to create the corresponding SPDMDBusResponder and initiate attestation only for the newly added device.\n\nFor removed responders, the discovery layer will call `notifyDeviceRemoved`. This method is expected to handle the responder removal by cancelling the corresponding spawned task and removing the responder entry from the manager state.",
